transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I received a prescription in the mail as far as a renewal, and I never asked for a renewal.

Speaker 1: Okay. What's your name and your date of birth?

Speaker 2: Mark Perez, 3/26/63.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. Perez, I do see that you have a prescription with us for the 50 milligrams of the Viagra,

Speaker 1: and it looks like the doctor did write your prescription with refills.

Speaker 2: So that's why you received another prescription.

Speaker 1: I didn't ask for refills, though.

Speaker 2: I mean, the first time I used it, why would I ask for refills?

Speaker 1: None of those are going to be any good.

Speaker 2: Well, that's how telehealth companies, that's industry standard that the prescription doesn't come with refills

Speaker 1: unless you call us to cancel everything entirely.

Speaker 2: Well, I didn't say that when I signed up.

Speaker 1: Regardless, I don't want refills.

Speaker 2: Okay. Do you not plan on taking it down the line?

Speaker 1: Because you're not obligated to get it every month.

Speaker 2: If I need it, I will renew it.

Speaker 1: I will get another prescription.

Speaker 2: Okay, no problem.

Speaker 1: I'll go ahead and cancel everything out.

Speaker 2: Just know that you'll have to restart again, and then the next time the doctor fee won't be covered.

Speaker 1: That's fine.

Speaker 2: Okay, I've gone ahead and canceled it for you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome. Have a good day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye-bye.
